1
00:01:51,524 --> 00:01:53,549
My dear children...

2
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:56,857
it is now better
than several years...

3
00:01:56,963 --> 00:01:59,124
since I moved to New York...

4
00:01:59,232 --> 00:02:01,928
and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.

5
00:02:03,536 --> 00:02:07,563
I hope you will come
to this ceremony of papal honors...

6
00:02:07,674 --> 00:02:09,562
given for my charitable work.

7
00:02:12,045 --> 00:02:15,469
The only wealth
in this world is children.

8
00:02:15,582 --> 00:02:19,541
More than all the money,
power on earth...

9
00:02:19,652 --> 00:02:21,540
you are my treasure.

10
00:02:23,756 --> 00:02:26,088
Anthony and Mary...

11
00:02:26,192 --> 00:02:28,524
although I entrusted
your education to your mother...

12
00:02:28,628 --> 00:02:30,994
for your own best interests...

13
00:02:31,097 --> 00:02:33,588
you know how I look forward
to seeing you...

14
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:36,760
and to a new period
of harmony in our lives.

15
00:02:38,204 --> 00:02:40,764
Perhaps you might
prevail upon your mother...

16
00:02:40,874 --> 00:02:43,172
to come to this celebration...

17
00:02:43,276 --> 00:02:45,801
and that from time to time...

18
00:02:45,912 --> 00:02:49,700
we can all see each other
at family functions.

19
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:54,480
Anyway, I remain,
your loving father.

20
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:26,380
Hail Mary, full of grace...

21
00:03:30,256 --> 00:03:32,247
blessed art Thou amongst women...

22
00:03:33,626 --> 00:03:37,722
and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb,Jesus.

23
00:03:37,830 --> 00:03:40,663
Holy Mary, mother of God...

24
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:43,133
pray for us sinners--

25
00:04:06,726 --> 00:04:10,082
Almighty God,
bless the insignia...

26
00:04:10,196 --> 00:04:12,756
of Saint Sebastian the Martyr...

27
00:04:12,865 --> 00:04:17,154
that it may contribute
to the sacredness of him...

28
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:19,192
to whom it is given.

29
00:04:31,618 --> 00:04:33,506
Do you, Michael...

30
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:36,748
promise to be faithful
to the noble purposes...

31
00:04:36,856 --> 00:04:38,778
of this order...

32
00:04:38,891 --> 00:04:42,019
to have a special care
for the poor, the needy...

33
00:04:42,128 --> 00:04:43,891
and those who are ill?

34
00:04:43,997 --> 00:04:45,794
l do so promise.

35
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:04,136
May the blessing
of Almighty God--

36
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:09,210
Father, Son, and Holy Spirit--

37
00:05:09,322 --> 00:05:13,486
descend upon you
and remain with you...

38
00:05:13,593 --> 00:05:14,958
forever.

39
00:05:15,061 --> 00:05:16,688
Amen.

40
00:06:48,521 --> 00:06:50,079
Vincent, our name's
not on the list.

41
00:06:53,626 --> 00:06:54,923
Write it in.

42
00:06:55,027 --> 00:06:57,518
Mancini. M-A-N-C-l-N-l.

43
00:06:59,298 --> 00:07:01,926
- ls there a problem?
- My name's not on the list.

44
00:07:02,034 --> 00:07:04,457
Then you have to
leave immediately.

45
00:07:04,570 --> 00:07:06,868
- No two ways about it.
- You want to dance?

46
00:07:06,973 --> 00:07:09,669
Joe, it's Vinnie.
lt's okay. These are our guests.

47
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:11,909
l'm sorry, Dave.

48
00:07:12,011 --> 00:07:14,900
lt's all right.
Vinnie, welcome to the party.

49
00:08:07,834 --> 00:08:09,233
Good to see you.

50
00:08:09,335 --> 00:08:12,190
lt's good to see you again.
This is my husband.

51
00:08:12,305 --> 00:08:14,193
This is my son, Anthony.

52
00:08:15,308 --> 00:08:18,197
The order of Saint Sebastian
is one of the highest honors...

53
00:08:18,311 --> 00:08:20,336
the Catholic Church
can bestow upon a layman.

54
00:08:20,446 --> 00:08:23,244
The award was first granted
by Pope Gregory--

55
00:08:23,349 --> 00:08:26,273
What about Mr. Corleone's connections
with Las Vegas gambling?

56
00:08:26,385 --> 00:08:28,717
Press kits have pictures--

57
00:08:28,821 --> 00:08:30,982
How about his involvement
with the underworld?

58
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:32,580
Cut the crap, huh?

59
00:08:32,658 --> 00:08:35,923
The pope,
the Holy Father himself...

60
00:08:36,028 --> 00:08:38,724
has this very day
blessed Michael Corleone.

61
00:08:38,831 --> 00:08:40,719
You think you know
better than the pope?

62
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,721
- Do it, do it.
- Vincent!

63
00:08:42,835 --> 00:08:45,224
- Yes?
- She loves you.

64
00:08:50,343 --> 00:08:51,833
- What'd he say?
- l love you too.

65
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:01,477
Hi, Vincent.
l remember you.

66
00:09:02,655 --> 00:09:04,179
You remember me?
From where?

67
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:06,679
When we were at
a party together.

68
00:09:06,792 --> 00:09:08,680
Did you come to the club?

69
00:09:08,794 --> 00:09:11,285
- No, it was a wedding.
- A wedding?

70
00:09:12,398 --> 00:09:15,890
l was eight, and you were 1 5.

71
00:09:16,002 --> 00:09:19,028
l had a lot of girlfriends
when l was 1 5.

72
00:09:19,138 --> 00:09:21,333
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially eight-year-olds.

73
00:09:23,476 --> 00:09:25,603
Where's Mary?

74
00:09:25,711 --> 00:09:28,100
Would somebody please hail Mary?

75
00:09:28,214 --> 00:09:30,409
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

76
00:09:30,516 --> 00:09:33,440
You know, you haven't
kissed me hello yet.

77
00:09:33,552 --> 00:09:36,680
- Relatives always kiss.
- Oh, now we're related?

78
00:09:36,789 --> 00:09:39,314
l'm your little cousin.

79
00:09:46,332 --> 00:09:48,061
Who's your father?

80
00:09:48,167 --> 00:09:50,863
l'll give you a hint.

81
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:53,495
- He's ltalian.
- Mary.

82
00:09:53,606 --> 00:09:56,461
Mary, we've been
waiting for you.

83
00:09:56,575 --> 00:09:58,668
Remember...

84
00:09:58,778 --> 00:10:00,575
keep your voice low.

85
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:03,205
Smile. Don't forget to smile.

86
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,764
Carissimi Amici...

87
00:10:22,868 --> 00:10:24,756
the honorary chairman...

88
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:27,134
of the Vito Corleone
Foundation...

89
00:10:27,239 --> 00:10:29,867
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

90
00:10:39,618 --> 00:10:40,573
Thanks.

91
00:10:42,254 --> 00:10:46,179
l think l inherited my father's love
for speechmaking...

92
00:10:46,292 --> 00:10:47,725
but here it goes.

93
00:10:48,894 --> 00:10:50,782
The Vito Corleone Foundation...

94
00:10:50,896 --> 00:10:53,490
helps the impoverished
of every country...

95
00:10:53,599 --> 00:10:55,988
gives grants to artists...

96
00:10:56,102 --> 00:10:58,400
funds medical research...

97
00:10:58,504 --> 00:11:03,237
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

98
00:11:03,342 --> 00:11:05,674
Archbishop Gilday...

99
00:11:05,778 --> 00:11:10,203
here is $ 1 00 million
for the poor of Sicily...

100
00:11:10,316 --> 00:11:12,511
in the name of Vito Corleone.

101
00:11:12,618 --> 00:11:15,416
Don't spend it all in one place.

102
00:11:37,009 --> 00:11:39,136
l'm so proud of you.

103
00:11:47,219 --> 00:11:50,643
You've done a wonderful thing
for Sicily.

104
00:11:50,756 --> 00:11:54,783
Let's just hope the money
gets to the people who need it.

105
00:11:54,894 --> 00:11:58,660
- Amen.
- But the most important part--

106
00:11:58,764 --> 00:12:00,686
Johnny Fontane!

107
00:12:09,642 --> 00:12:11,405
Thank you very much.

108
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:14,399
l'm happy to be here with you,
and l'd like you to join me...

109
00:12:14,513 --> 00:12:18,142
in honoring
commendatore Michael Corleone.

110
00:12:22,588 --> 00:12:25,978
l have something special
for our host and godfather.

111
00:12:26,092 --> 00:12:28,617
l just happen to know
his favorite song.

112
00:12:28,727 --> 00:12:30,649
Michael, where are you going?
lt's your favorite song.

113
00:12:30,763 --> 00:12:34,187
l'm off here to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

114
00:12:35,935 --> 00:12:38,267
It's your favorite song.
It's salsiccia's own.

115
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:40,201
We're getting
a salsiccia sandwich.

116
00:12:40,306 --> 00:12:41,739
l'll be back.

117
00:12:46,078 --> 00:12:48,967
A rose must remain

118
00:12:49,081 --> 00:12:51,641
With the sun and the rain

119
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:56,540
Or its lovely promise
won't come true

120
00:12:57,723 --> 00:13:00,487
To each his own

121
00:13:00,593 --> 00:13:04,723
To each his own

122
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:08,425
And my own is you

123
00:13:16,175 --> 00:13:18,200
Hello, Kay.

124
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:31,114
Congratulations, Michael.
That's really quite an honor.

125
00:13:31,223 --> 00:13:34,147
lt's a little expensive,
wouldn't you say?

126
00:13:36,829 --> 00:13:38,751
Cake?

127
00:13:38,864 --> 00:13:40,525
No, thank you.

128
00:13:54,180 --> 00:13:57,069
- Been a long time, hasn't it?
- Yeah.

129
00:13:57,183 --> 00:13:59,572
Eight years.

130
00:13:59,685 --> 00:14:01,573
You look wonderful.

131
00:14:05,357 --> 00:14:07,723
Your son has something
he wants to talk to you about.

132
00:14:07,826 --> 00:14:10,158
l came here for him.

133
00:14:12,631 --> 00:14:14,519
Nice to see you.
Thank you.

134
00:14:18,938 --> 00:14:21,771
If a flame is to grow

135
00:14:21,874 --> 00:14:25,230
There must be a glow

136
00:14:25,344 --> 00:14:27,938
To open each door

137
00:14:28,047 --> 00:14:30,777
There's a key

138
00:14:30,883 --> 00:14:33,738
I need you, I know

139
00:14:33,852 --> 00:14:36,480
I can't let you go

140
00:14:44,430 --> 00:14:47,490
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- Nothing, except he doesn't want it.

141
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,489
He wants his life
to be in music.

142
00:14:51,870 --> 00:14:54,259
Music is great.
l love music...

143
00:14:54,373 --> 00:14:56,762
but he should finish
what he started.

144
00:14:58,143 --> 00:15:01,476
- l'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

145
00:15:01,580 --> 00:15:03,207
- Professional singer?
- That's right.

146
00:15:03,315 --> 00:15:06,739
And what happens if you fail?

147
00:15:06,852 --> 00:15:08,774
l won't fail.

148
00:15:08,887 --> 00:15:11,219
- Men always believe that.
- l know.

149
00:15:11,323 --> 00:15:13,211
lf you have a law degree...

150
00:15:13,325 --> 00:15:15,213
you're taking out
insurance.

151
00:15:15,327 --> 00:15:17,352
After that, you can do anything--
work for me--

152
00:15:17,463 --> 00:15:19,658
l will never work for you.

153
00:15:19,765 --> 00:15:21,596
l have bad memories.

154
00:15:24,036 --> 00:15:26,664
Every family has bad memories.

155
00:15:30,476 --> 00:15:32,569
l will always be your son...

156
00:15:32,678 --> 00:15:37,240
but l will never have anything
to do with your business.

157
00:15:37,349 --> 00:15:41,206
Anthony, finish the law degree.

158
00:16:00,873 --> 00:16:05,196
That he got from you,
that ''no.''

159
00:16:08,013 --> 00:16:11,210
You could have helped me
to convince him, Kay.

160
00:16:11,317 --> 00:16:13,205
Oh, yeah.
Convince him of what?

161
00:16:13,319 --> 00:16:15,810
Of what?

162
00:16:15,888 --> 00:16:18,652
He throws his life away.

163
00:16:18,757 --> 00:16:20,713
He throws greatness away.

164
00:16:21,794 --> 00:16:24,752
This is greatness?

165
00:16:24,863 --> 00:16:26,751
Now that you're
so respectable...

166
00:16:26,865 --> 00:16:29,231
l think you're more dangerous
than you ever were.

167
00:16:29,335 --> 00:16:31,291
ln fact, l preferred you
when you were just...

168
00:16:31,403 --> 00:16:33,735
a common Mafia hood.

169
00:16:37,209 --> 00:16:40,565
- Now can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

170
00:16:47,386 --> 00:16:50,344
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

171
00:16:56,628 --> 00:16:59,984
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

172
00:17:00,099 --> 00:17:02,693
l didn't come to see you disguised
by your church.

173
00:17:02,801 --> 00:17:05,190
l think that was
a shameful ceremony.

174
00:17:09,475 --> 00:17:12,273
l spent my life
protecting my son.

175
00:17:12,378 --> 00:17:16,269
l spent my life
protecting my family!

176
00:17:16,382 --> 00:17:19,271
Let's be reasonable.

177
00:17:19,385 --> 00:17:23,173
That's your big thing,
isn't it, Michael?

178
00:17:23,288 --> 00:17:27,452
Reason backed up by murder.

179
00:17:27,559 --> 00:17:29,220
Oh, God.

180
00:17:30,496 --> 00:17:33,056
God, you hate me. You hate me.

181
00:17:33,832 --> 00:17:35,925
l don't hate you.

182
00:17:37,169 --> 00:17:38,568
l dread you.

183
00:17:42,975 --> 00:17:46,399
l did what l could, Kay, to protect...

184
00:17:46,512 --> 00:17:49,174
all of you from the horrors
of this world.

185
00:17:50,582 --> 00:17:52,470
But you became my horror.

186
00:18:02,261 --> 00:18:04,593
Our children still love you, though.

187
00:18:04,696 --> 00:18:06,391
Especially Mary.

188
00:18:09,101 --> 00:18:10,659
That's something.

189
00:18:13,205 --> 00:18:17,027
We can build on that,
for their sake.

190
00:18:20,813 --> 00:18:22,440
Let's try.

191
00:18:22,548 --> 00:18:25,779
Only if you let Tony go free
to have his own life...

192
00:18:26,885 --> 00:18:28,011
away from you.

193
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:37,148
l'll let Tony go.

194
00:18:39,665 --> 00:18:41,292
Thank you.

195
00:19:19,872 --> 00:19:21,794
You could hurt somebody
with those.

196
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:25,164
Let me show you around.

197
00:19:25,277 --> 00:19:27,643
Can you get me an interview
with Michael Corleone?

198
00:19:27,746 --> 00:19:30,601
No. l'm a relative,
but l can't do that.

199
00:19:30,716 --> 00:19:33,344
What else could l do for you?

200
00:19:33,452 --> 00:19:36,046
- Handsome but useless.
- Oh, yeah?

201
00:19:36,154 --> 00:19:39,351
- That's okay. l'll gamble.
- You like to gamble?

202
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:43,485
Let's go to Atlantic City. lt's my town.
l'll show you how to gamble.

203
00:19:43,595 --> 00:19:45,961
How will l know
what numbers to bet?

204
00:19:46,064 --> 00:19:47,827
Do l look like a loser?

205
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:49,423
Well--

206
00:19:51,837 --> 00:19:54,260
That's a spooky-looking
guy there.

207
00:19:54,373 --> 00:19:57,900
What's a guy like that doing
at Michael Corleone's house?

208
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:00,342
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.
- You know that guy?

209
00:20:00,445 --> 00:20:02,572
Yeah, l know that guy.

210
00:20:02,681 --> 00:20:05,570
That guy's name
is Anthony Squigiliaro.

211
00:20:05,684 --> 00:20:07,606
They call him ''the Ant.''

212
00:20:07,719 --> 00:20:11,052
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

213
00:20:19,197 --> 00:20:20,960
Don Altobello.

214
00:20:22,601 --> 00:20:24,990
l come to pay my respects.

215
00:20:29,508 --> 00:20:31,931
You honor my father's friendship.

216
00:20:32,044 --> 00:20:34,205
Where is my goddaughter?

217
00:20:38,884 --> 00:20:43,150
lt was not so long ago
l held you in these old hands.

218
00:20:48,627 --> 00:20:51,255
No, no.
l stand. l stand.

219
00:20:51,363 --> 00:20:54,787
Michael, l lost
all the venom...

220
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,788
all the juice of youth.

221
00:20:56,902 --> 00:20:58,927
l lost the lust
for women...

222
00:20:59,037 --> 00:21:02,529
and now my mind is clear.

223
00:21:02,641 --> 00:21:05,530
My duty to God is clear.

224
00:21:05,644 --> 00:21:09,034
l have a special favor to ask.

225
00:21:10,716 --> 00:21:14,948
Can l attach my name...

226
00:21:15,053 --> 00:21:17,942
to the Vito Corleone Foundation...

227
00:21:18,056 --> 00:21:20,786
so that you and l can be joined...

228
00:21:20,892 --> 00:21:23,588
in name and spirit?

229
00:21:25,931 --> 00:21:27,626
One million dollars.

230
00:21:33,772 --> 00:21:36,195
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello...

231
00:21:36,308 --> 00:21:38,196
you have such a heart.

232
00:21:40,712 --> 00:21:43,340
Come, let's go
and sample some of it.

233
00:21:51,556 --> 00:21:55,048
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

234
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:58,550
Good.
l have a tendency to worry.

235
00:21:58,664 --> 00:22:01,462
We've increased our position
substantially...

236
00:22:01,566 --> 00:22:02,726
and naturally, l worry.

237
00:22:02,834 --> 00:22:04,461
Come along now.
Stop worrying.

238
00:22:04,569 --> 00:22:06,958
We have an agreement.

239
00:22:07,072 --> 00:22:09,734
Good. How do you think
l got this gray hair?

240
00:22:09,841 --> 00:22:11,138
Mr. Corleone.

241
00:22:11,243 --> 00:22:13,302
- Two seconds.
- Frank, how are you?

242
00:22:13,412 --> 00:22:15,903
Thanks for your swimming pool
contribution...

243
00:22:16,014 --> 00:22:20,246
and we need your help on
Sam Wallace's candidacy for a judgeship.

244
00:22:20,352 --> 00:22:22,582
- We always can use a good judge.
- Thank you.

245
00:22:22,688 --> 00:22:24,553
Andrew.

246
00:22:24,656 --> 00:22:26,988
Excellency, my godson,
Andrew Hagen...

247
00:22:27,092 --> 00:22:28,980
my brother Tom Hagen's
eldest boy...

248
00:22:29,094 --> 00:22:32,484
and he's been assistant
to Bishop Breelan three years now.

249
00:22:32,597 --> 00:22:34,929
He's hoping for
a Vatican assignment.

250
00:22:35,033 --> 00:22:37,627
There's always a place in Rome
for a fine priest.

251
00:22:37,736 --> 00:22:40,159
His mother, Theresa Hagen.
Bishop Gilday.

252
00:22:40,272 --> 00:22:42,934
Thank you.
lt's an honor to meet you.

253
00:22:43,041 --> 00:22:47,501
Mr. Corleone, hi.
Grace Hamilton.

254
00:22:47,612 --> 00:22:50,103
Vincent Mancini promised
he'd tell you about me...

255
00:22:50,182 --> 00:22:52,446
that maybe you'd see me.

256
00:22:52,551 --> 00:22:54,314
Vincent Mancini call about her?

257
00:22:54,419 --> 00:22:55,818
