01:23:49,838 --> 01:23:53,626
l'm too old to know anything
about those new people.

1009
01:23:53,742 --> 01:23:58,372
l must accept my age
and grow my olives and tomatoes.

1010
01:23:59,648 --> 01:24:04,403
- We're not that old.
- But you're very ill.

1011
01:24:07,188 --> 01:24:09,520
Let me see what can be done.

1012
01:24:09,624 --> 01:24:14,049
Let me work to make your path
a little easier.

1013
01:24:14,162 --> 01:24:17,427
Your friendship does that always.

1014
01:24:17,532 --> 01:24:19,420
That makes me happy.

1015
01:24:22,370 --> 01:24:23,803
You were wrong about him.

1016
01:24:25,140 --> 01:24:28,530
l trust too much.
That's always been my fault.

1017
01:24:38,320 --> 01:24:40,311
Treachery is everywhere.

1018
01:24:40,422 --> 01:24:46,110
You still have your fingers
on the strings, even now.

1019
01:24:46,227 --> 01:24:48,616
Let's see more of each other.

1020
01:24:50,999 --> 01:24:53,388
- In Sicily?
- In Sicily.

1021
01:25:46,692 --> 01:25:49,024
How are you?

1022
01:25:49,128 --> 01:25:51,653
Don Bendino, my old friend.

1023
01:26:22,995 --> 01:26:25,054
l wanted to bring you here...

1024
01:26:25,164 --> 01:26:28,793
so that my old friend and protector,
Don Tommasino...

1025
01:26:28,901 --> 01:26:30,789
could advise us.

1026
01:26:49,121 --> 01:26:53,080
The bloodbath in Atlantic City
left New York a mess.

1027
01:26:53,192 --> 01:26:56,650
Now,Joey Zasa at least was running
a fairly tight ship.

1028
01:26:56,762 --> 01:27:00,254
But now that he's out of the picture,
we're obligated to step in.

1029
01:27:00,366 --> 01:27:02,425
Step back in?

1030
01:27:02,535 --> 01:27:04,924
lf we don't,
the Chinese and Colombians will.

1031
01:27:36,235 --> 01:27:39,966
Our ships must all sail
in the same direction.

1032
01:27:41,273 --> 01:27:44,333
ltalian politics have had
these kind of men for centuries.

1033
01:27:44,443 --> 01:27:46,934
They are the true Mafia.

1034
01:27:47,046 --> 01:27:50,402
The archbishop and the Vatican Bank,
that's the big problem.

1035
01:27:50,516 --> 01:27:54,839
They're the same problem.
BJ, they're connected.

1036
01:27:54,954 --> 01:27:57,980
The archbishop has
very powerful friends.

1037
01:28:00,993 --> 01:28:02,824
They totally protect him.

1038
01:28:28,454 --> 01:28:31,048
l will go see
this Cardinal Lamberto...

1039
01:28:31,157 --> 01:28:34,012
and see if we can work things out
in a civilized way.

1040
01:28:35,928 --> 01:28:37,987
You honor your agreements...

1041
01:28:38,097 --> 01:28:40,622
but these people
you're dealing with are crooks.

1042
01:28:40,733 --> 01:28:42,621
They have no honor.

1043
01:28:45,738 --> 01:28:47,228
My word is final.

1044
01:29:24,610 --> 01:29:26,703
l've invited you all here...

1045
01:29:26,812 --> 01:29:31,044
to celebrate my son's
first appearance in an opera house.

1046
01:29:31,150 --> 01:29:32,708
- We're playing Philadelphia.
- He'll be appearing...

1047
01:29:32,818 --> 01:29:34,774
- What's Philadelphia?
- in about three weeks...

1048
01:29:34,887 --> 01:29:36,946
Seven cards, two down,
four up, one down...

1049
01:29:37,056 --> 01:29:39,012
- at the Theatre Massimo...
- deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

1050
01:29:39,125 --> 01:29:41,753
in the opera ''Cavallaria''Rusticana.

1051
01:29:41,861 --> 01:29:45,683
lt's Cavalleria Rusticana.

1052
01:29:45,798 --> 01:29:48,722
l think l got tickets
to the wrong opera.

1053
01:29:48,834 --> 01:29:51,997
l've been in New York too long.
Anyway...

1054
01:29:52,104 --> 01:29:55,665
you will all receive tickets,
so come on time.

1055
01:29:55,775 --> 01:29:57,663
Dad, l've got a present for you.

1056
01:30:01,847 --> 01:30:03,974
lt comes from the town of Corleone...

1057
01:30:04,083 --> 01:30:06,108
and it's authentic Sicilian.

1058
01:30:07,219 --> 01:30:10,780
And l learned it for you.

1059
01:31:40,045 --> 01:31:44,141
She was wonderful, beautiful,
and I loved her.

1060
01:31:44,250 --> 01:31:46,480
Then she died.

1061
01:31:46,585 --> 01:31:50,180
My trusted bodyguard...

1062
01:31:50,289 --> 01:31:53,520
planted a bomb in my car.

1063
01:31:53,626 --> 01:31:55,514
She drove it before l did.

1064
01:31:57,129 --> 01:32:00,792
Why is such a beautiful country
so violent?

1065
01:32:00,900 --> 01:32:02,458
History.

1066
01:32:02,568 --> 01:32:04,832
Mom was telling me about the old days.

1067
01:32:04,937 --> 01:32:09,067
- Your biggest worry was passing exams.
- Yes, it was then.

1068
01:32:09,174 --> 01:32:11,165
l worry about you now.

1069
01:32:12,845 --> 01:32:16,406
Mary, you're such a warmhearted girl.
You always were.

1070
01:32:16,515 --> 01:32:20,246
- l love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

1071
01:32:24,256 --> 01:32:26,019
l really love him.

1072
01:32:27,493 --> 01:32:31,725
- He's your first cousin.
- Then l love him first.

1073
01:32:31,830 --> 01:32:34,560
Mary, you can't see him.

1074
01:32:34,667 --> 01:32:38,023
Just don't see him anymore.

1075
01:32:38,137 --> 01:32:41,959
He's right.
lt's too dangerous.

1076
01:32:44,543 --> 01:32:47,876
Listen to me.
You can't see him anymore.

1077
01:32:47,980 --> 01:32:49,709
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

1078
01:32:51,550 --> 01:32:53,643
Please, promise me.

1079
01:32:54,920 --> 01:32:57,218
- Obey me on this.
- No, Dad!

1080
01:33:02,661 --> 01:33:06,984
Mary's smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

1081
01:33:43,969 --> 01:33:47,166
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

1082
01:33:47,272 --> 01:33:49,934
- l want you to do something for me.
- Okay.

1083
01:33:50,042 --> 01:33:52,465
lt's dangerous.

1084
01:33:52,578 --> 01:33:56,503
Good, l'm in.
What do you need?

1085
01:33:56,615 --> 01:34:00,312
l want you to sell your soul
to Don Altobello...

1086
01:34:00,419 --> 01:34:02,307
to betray me.

1087
01:34:05,657 --> 01:34:08,421
He'd never believe me.
Here.

1088
01:34:08,527 --> 01:34:10,757
- That depends.
- Sit down.

1089
01:34:13,999 --> 01:34:15,887
l have an idea.

1090
01:34:17,169 --> 01:34:21,060
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

1091
01:34:24,843 --> 01:34:26,731
Arrange a meeting.

1092
01:34:29,281 --> 01:34:34,412
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

1093
01:34:34,520 --> 01:34:37,409
- You ask for his help.
- What problems?

1094
01:34:39,591 --> 01:34:41,479
That you want to run away
with my daughter.

1095
01:34:43,128 --> 01:34:47,519
Only you know that if you do,
l will become your enemy.

1096
01:34:52,271 --> 01:34:54,501
You know l would never do that,
Uncle Mike.

1097
01:34:54,606 --> 01:34:55,664
l know.

1098
01:34:56,942 --> 01:34:59,866
You ask Altobello to speak to me...

1099
01:34:59,978 --> 01:35:01,934
to further the marriage.

1100
01:35:02,047 --> 01:35:04,345
But you're cousins, after all.

1101
01:35:04,450 --> 01:35:07,874
Michael was always
a little old-fashioned.

1102
01:35:07,986 --> 01:35:09,044
Explain to him how...

1103
01:35:09,154 --> 01:35:11,418
you could never be a part
of my legitimate world...

1104
01:35:11,523 --> 01:35:13,081
that you want your own family.

1105
01:35:13,192 --> 01:35:17,083
l could straighten out
what Zasa left behind.

1106
01:35:18,831 --> 01:35:21,220
l could use your friendship
to persuade him.

1107
01:35:22,768 --> 01:35:25,157
l would be indebted to you forever.

1108
01:35:27,639 --> 01:35:31,530
Corleones know the value
of such a friend.

1109
01:35:33,011 --> 01:35:35,400
So then you would work for me?

1110
01:35:44,056 --> 01:35:45,717
Remember...

1111
01:35:45,824 --> 01:35:50,750
if he hints that he wants you
to betray me, get insulted...

1112
01:35:50,863 --> 01:35:52,785
because that's his trap.

1113
01:36:00,439 --> 01:36:03,328
You're not telling me
the whole truth.

1114
01:36:06,912 --> 01:36:10,643
lsn't it true, with Michael gone...

1115
01:36:10,749 --> 01:36:13,138
the girl controls everything?

1116
01:36:16,655 --> 01:36:18,748
You leave the girl out of this.

1117
01:36:18,857 --> 01:36:22,247
Of course, you love her,
and she loves you.

1118
01:36:43,182 --> 01:36:45,571
l guessed it, huh?

1119
01:36:47,219 --> 01:36:50,609
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.

1120
01:36:50,722 --> 01:36:53,350
l'm gonna be learning a lot
from you.

1121
01:36:53,458 --> 01:36:56,188
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

1122
01:36:58,964 --> 01:37:02,127
lt's my duty to make
the introductions.

1123
01:37:09,107 --> 01:37:10,995
Don Lucchesi.

1124
01:37:13,845 --> 01:37:16,473
Don Altobello tells me
you have a good character...

1125
01:37:16,582 --> 01:37:19,642
strong,
a man of respect.

1126
01:37:19,751 --> 01:37:23,539
This is the hero
who put Joey Zasa in his grave.

1127
01:37:23,655 --> 01:37:27,944
lf we'd have known of his existence,
we would never have backed Joey.

1128
01:37:28,060 --> 01:37:29,948
No one wants another Joe.

1129
01:37:31,897 --> 01:37:33,194
Let me be your friend.

1130
01:37:34,933 --> 01:37:37,857
Even the strongest man needs friends.

1131
01:37:37,970 --> 01:37:40,359
l'm flattered.

1132
01:37:40,472 --> 01:37:43,066
You're a man of finance and politics,
Don Lucchesi.

1133
01:37:43,175 --> 01:37:45,063
These are things l don't understand.

1134
01:37:46,845 --> 01:37:48,073
You understand guns.

1135
01:37:49,014 --> 01:37:51,039
Finance is a gun.

1136
01:37:51,149 --> 01:37:55,745
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

1137
01:38:00,292 --> 01:38:01,520
How can l help?

1138
01:38:07,199 --> 01:38:09,793
Blessed is the peacemaker...

1139
01:38:09,901 --> 01:38:12,790
for he can be called
the child of God.

1140
01:38:49,007 --> 01:38:52,568
l trusted this business arrangement
with the archbishop.

1141
01:38:52,678 --> 01:38:57,775
l trusted him. l was sure
his honesty was beyond a doubt.

1142
01:38:57,883 --> 01:39:03,173
But, as you see,
l'm now the victim of a swindle.

1143
01:39:03,288 --> 01:39:05,176
He's stalling me.

1144
01:39:05,290 --> 01:39:09,249
Vast money have gone to the pezzonovante
in high political places...

1145
01:39:09,361 --> 01:39:12,091
and the Vatican Bank
is the guarantor.

1146
01:39:12,197 --> 01:39:17,453
lf what you say is true,
there will be a great scandal.

1147
01:39:19,438 --> 01:39:24,569
Look at this stone. lt has been lying
in the water for a very long time...

1148
01:39:24,676 --> 01:39:28,567
but the water has not penetrated it.

1149
01:39:32,617 --> 01:39:36,508
Look, perfectly dry.

1150
01:39:37,756 --> 01:39:40,122
The same thing has happened
to men in Europe.

1151
01:39:40,225 --> 01:39:45,117
For centuries, they have been
surrounded by Christianity...

1152
01:39:45,230 --> 01:39:47,755
but Christ has not penetrated.

1153
01:39:47,866 --> 01:39:51,256
Christ doesn't live within them.

1154
01:39:55,307 --> 01:39:57,434
- What's happening?
- ls it possible...

1155
01:39:57,542 --> 01:40:00,466
that you could get me something sweet.

1156
01:40:00,579 --> 01:40:02,968
Orange juice, anything, a candy.

1157
01:40:06,551 --> 01:40:08,610
l have a little trouble with diabetes.

1158
01:40:12,591 --> 01:40:14,479
Blood sugar goes low.

1159
01:40:15,627 --> 01:40:17,515
l understand.

1160
01:40:40,018 --> 01:40:43,681
When l'm under stress,
sometimes this happens.

1161
01:40:43,789 --> 01:40:45,677
l understand.

1162
01:40:47,526 --> 01:40:50,916
To come to you
on such a delicate matter...

1163
01:40:54,065 --> 01:40:57,023
accusations against your archbishop.

1164
01:40:57,135 --> 01:40:59,194
lt was difficult for me.

1165
01:41:00,439 --> 01:41:02,634
The mind suffers...

1166
01:41:02,741 --> 01:41:06,370
and the body cries out.

1167
01:41:11,216 --> 01:41:13,275
That's true.

1168
01:41:14,753 --> 01:41:19,076
Would you like to make
your confession?

1169
01:41:25,730 --> 01:41:27,789
Your Eminence, l'm--

1170
01:41:31,603 --> 01:41:33,332
lt's been so long.

1171
01:41:33,438 --> 01:41:36,828
l wouldn't know where to--

1172
01:41:38,577 --> 01:41:40,465
lt's been 30 years.

1173
01:41:42,614 --> 01:41:45,105
l'd use up too much of your time,
l think.

1174
01:41:45,217 --> 01:41:48,311
l always have time to save souls.

1175
01:41:49,721 --> 01:41:52,610
Well, l'm beyond redemption.

1176
01:42:03,935 --> 01:42:08,895
l hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

1177
01:42:09,007 --> 01:42:12,829
Sometimes the desire to confess
is overwhelming...

1178
01:42:12,944 --> 01:42:15,333
and we must seize the moment.

1179
01:42:20,352 --> 01:42:24,880
What is the point of confessing
if l don't repent?

1180
01:42:26,591 --> 01:42:29,890
l hear you are a practical man.

1181
01:42:29,995 --> 01:42:33,055
What have you got to lose, huh?

1182
01:42:43,975 --> 01:42:46,205
Go on.

1183
01:42:52,150 --> 01:42:53,549
l...

1184
01:42:54,686 --> 01:42:56,574
betrayed my wife.

1185
01:42:58,223 --> 01:43:00,111
Go on, my son.

1186
01:43:05,530 --> 01:43:07,418
l betrayed myself.

1187
01:43:10,302 --> 01:43:12,190
l killed men.

1188
01:43:15,941 --> 01:43:18,330
And l ordered men to be killed.

1189
01:43:19,978 --> 01:43:21,866
Go on, my son, go on.

1190
01:43:28,019 --> 01:43:29,247
lt's useless.

1191
01:43:31,323 --> 01:43:33,211
Go on, my son.

1192
01:43:34,326 --> 01:43:36,214
l killed--

1193
01:43:40,966 --> 01:43:44,629
l ordered the death of my brother.

1194
01:43:44,736 --> 01:43:46,624
He injured me.

1195
01:43:48,039 --> 01:43:50,633
l killed my mother's son.

1196
01:43:52,010 --> 01:43:54,103
l killed my father's son.

1197
01:44:04,823 --> 01:44:06,848
Your sins are terrible...

1198
01:44:06,958 --> 01:44:09,518
and it is just
that you suffer.

1199
01:44:10,795 --> 01:44:13,184
Your life could be redeemed...

1200
01:44:14,432 --> 01:44:16,320
but l know
that you don't believe that.

1201
01:44:16,434 --> 01:44:18,322
You will not change.

1202
01:45:13,925 --> 01:45:17,816
All my life
l kept trying to go up in society...

1203
01:45:19,064 --> 01:45:22,454
where everything higher up
was legal, straight.

1204
01:45:23,935 --> 01:45:26,995
But the higher l go,
the more crooked it becomes.

1205
01:45:30,275 --> 01:45:32,334
Where the hell does it end?

1206
01:45:41,419 --> 01:45:44,308
Killing each other
for centuries here.

1207
01:45:46,157 --> 01:45:50,514
For money, for pride, for family.

1208
01:45:53,598 --> 01:45:57,489
To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzonovante.

1209
01:46:04,642 --> 01:46:06,701
l made confession, Connie.

1210
01:46:07,812 --> 01:46:10,440
l confessed my sins.

1211
01:46:11,549 --> 01:46:14,040
Why, Michael?
That's not like you.

1212
01:46:14,152 --> 01:46:17,508
You don't have to confess your sins
to a stranger.

1213
01:46:17,622 --> 01:46:19,055
lt was the man.

1214
01:46:20,458 --> 01:46:22,585
A good man...

1215
01:46:22,694 --> 01:46:24,582
a true priest.

1216
01:46:28,299 --> 01:46:30,187
He can change things.

1217
01:46:35,573 --> 01:46:37,302
You know...

1218
01:46:37,408 --> 01:46:40,798
sometimes l think of poor Fredo--
drowned.

1219
01:46:42,380 --> 01:46:44,268
lt was God's will.

1220
01:46:46,151 --> 01:46:48,540
lt was a terrible accident.

1221
01:46:49,654 --> 01:46:51,542
But it's finished.

1222
01:46:56,961 --> 01:46:58,849
Michael, l love you.

1223
01:47:01,232 --> 01:47:03,120
l'll always help you.

1224
01:47:12,944 --> 01:47:14,832
lt's okay.

1225
01:49:54,973 --> 01:49:57,464
- Welcome.
- How are you?

1226
01:49:57,575 --> 01:50:01,067
- Mary, l missed you.
- l missed you too.

1227
01:50:01,179 --> 01:50:03,067
- Hello, Michael.
- Hello.

1228
01:50:03,181 --> 01:50:05,240
- Mom, look at this.
- What?

1229
01:50:06,918 --> 01:50:08,647
Oh, my--

1230
01:50:08,753 --> 01:50:10,880
You know, it's too bad
that Douglas couldn't be with us.

1231
01:50:10,989 --> 01:50:14,686
No, l know. He wanted to come very much,
but he had a very important trial.

1232
01:50:14,792 --> 01:50:17,920
- l know he wanted to come.
- l know.

1233
01:50:18,029 --> 01:50:19,917
- The car is--
- Okay.

1234
01:50:21,966 --> 01:50:26,027
Well, your son's an artist, huh?

1235
01:50:26,137 --> 01:50:28,230
Oh, yes, thanks to you.

1236
01:50:28,339 --> 01:50:29,738
Oh, what for?

1237
01:50:30,908 --> 01:50:33,172
For making me let him go.

1238
01:50:33,277 --> 01:50:35,165
Oh, well.

1239
01:50:35,279 --> 01:50:39,010
After all these years, here l am
in Sicily for the first time.

1240
01:50:39,117 --> 01:50:41,506
- l want a picture of you together.
- Okay.

1241
01:50:44,188 --> 01:50:46,076
Hey, Dad, smile.

1242
01:50:50,061 --> 01:50:53,292
l see you still have Al Neri.
Why?

1243
01:50:54,732 --> 01:50:58,964
Well, l need him. He helps me
get in and out of the car.

1244
01:50:59,070 --> 01:51:01,368
He carries my briefcase.

1245
01:51:01,472 --> 01:51:04,168
You're still a liar, Michael.

1246
01:51:04,275 --> 01:51:07,733
Let me show you Sicily--
the real Sicily.

1247
01:51:07,845 --> 01:51:10,643
Maybe you'll understand
the family history a little better.

1248
01:51:10,748 --> 01:51:13,137
l think l understand it well enough.

1249
01:52:05,169 --> 01:52:08,559
Anthony, l have something
you made for me...

1250
01:52:09,774 --> 01:52:11,662
a very long time ago.

1251
01:52:12,844 --> 01:52:15,972
- To bring you luck.
- Thanks.

1252
01:52:19,717 --> 01:52:21,275
You saved it, huh?

1253
01:52:21,385 --> 01:52:23,876
- Remember?
- l remember.

1254
01:52:26,424 --> 01:52:28,312
Thank you.

1255
01:52:30,595 --> 01:52:31,994
Proud of you.

1256
01:52:32,930 --> 01:52:34,488
Thank you.

1257
01:52:50,681 --> 01:52:53,309
- Are they as good as they look?
- They're better.

1258
01:52:53,417 --> 01:52:55,942
They're the best.

1259
01:52:56,053 --> 01:52:58,248
As long as they're around,
Uncle Michael is safe.

1260
01:52:58,389 --> 01:52:59,754
Good-bye.

1261
01:53:02,860 --> 01:53:04,816
Tell your father
l'll be back for dinner.

1262
01:53:06,597 --> 01:53:09,259
- Have fun.
- Tell Tony to be sure and wait for me.

1263
01:53:09,367 --> 01:53:11,995
Okay, l will.

1264
01:53:12,103 --> 01:53:14,401
Bye, Mom!

1265
01:53:14,505 --> 01:53:16,735
At your service.

1266
01:53:20,344 --> 01:53:23,734
lf l see Dad,
l'll tell him you left.

1267
01:53:28,953 --> 01:53:32,878
You're the only one left in this family
with my father's strength.

1268
01:53:35,126 --> 01:53:39,722
lf anything happens to Michael,
l want you to strike back.

1269
01:53:42,200 --> 01:53:43,758
l'll have everything ready.

1270
01:53:47,538 --> 01:53:49,426
You swear?

1271
01:53:56,547 --> 01:53:58,606
l swear to you.

1272
01:54:28,813 --> 01:54:30,701
Here it is.

1273
01:54:32,116 --> 01:54:34,175
The house where my father was born.

1274
01:54:35,820 --> 01:54:40,211
This is where they came to take him
when he was a boy...

1275
01:54:40,324 --> 01:54:42,212
to kill him.

1276
01:54:44,528 --> 01:54:47,918
Wait, listen to that.

1277
01:55:08,185 --> 01:55:11,643
You know, Mary's in love.

1278
01:55:11,756 --> 01:55:14,281
Yes, l know.

1279
01:55:14,392 --> 01:55:19,523
With a handsome young ltalian man
with dark eyes.

1280
01:55:19,630 --> 01:55:21,518
l won't allow it.

1281
01:55:24,335 --> 01:55:28,032
lt's wrong.
lt's wrong, and it's dangerous.

1282
01:56:00,371 --> 01:56:02,032
Honor, huh?

1283
01:56:21,492 --> 01:56:24,450
You know, l remember the time
you came to my parents' house...

1284
01:56:24,562 --> 01:56:27,861
and you took me into that room
and told me about the family business...

1285
01:56:27,965 --> 01:56:31,662
and how you were never going to have
anything to do with it.

1286
01:56:31,769 --> 01:56:34,101
You sounded like Tony.

1287
01:56:34,205 --> 01:56:36,093
l was a lot like Tony.

1288
01:56:43,714 --> 01:56:46,672
- l can barely see. Kay.
- What?

1289
01:56:46,784 --> 01:56:49,446
- You mind driving?
- No. What's wrong?

1290
01:56:49,553 --> 01:56:53,182
My eyes-- sometimes
they're all right, and then--

1291
01:56:53,290 --> 01:56:56,418
- Sure.
- Listen, l have to see Don Tommasino.

1292
01:56:58,496 --> 01:57:00,259
Oh, my God!

1293
01:57:00,364 --> 01:57:01,763
Well--

1294
01:57:02,933 --> 01:57:06,323
- There's no bodyguards today.
- l really snuck away.

1295
01:57:59,523 --> 01:58:01,286
- How are you?
- Hi.

1296
01:58:01,392 --> 01:58:03,280
- Kay, this is Calo, my old friend.
- How do you do?

1297
01:58:03,394 --> 01:58:05,282
One of my bodyguards
in the old days.

1298
01:58:10,701 --> 01:58:12,100
- We can wait here.
- You want drink?

1299
01:58:12,203 --> 01:58:15,593
- Yes. Shall we go in?
- Sure.

1300
01:58:18,175 --> 01:58:20,564
l spent a lot of time in this room...

1301
01:58:22,913 --> 01:58:24,642
thinking of you.

1302
01:58:27,785 --> 01:58:30,345
And then you got married.

1303
01:58:33,524 --> 01:58:35,082
l still thought of you.

1304
01:58:35,860 --> 01:58:37,748
What's in that room?

1305
01:58:41,565 --> 01:58:45,854
l know this is dangerous for you.
This is Sicily.

1306
01:58:48,205 --> 01:58:50,594
- l love this country.
- Why?

1307
01:58:53,310 --> 01:58:56,666
Well, all through history...

1308
01:58:56,780 --> 01:58:59,112
terrible things
have happened to these people.

1309
01:58:59,216 --> 01:59:02,014
Terrible injustices.

1310
01:59:03,120 --> 01:59:08,353
But they still expect good
rather than bad will happen to them.

1311
01:59:08,459 --> 01:59:10,848
Sort of like me and you, huh?

1312
01:59:14,932 --> 01:59:18,288
- How so?
- l'm still here, right?

1313
01:59:18,402 --> 01:59:19,892
We do have a bad history.

1314
01:59:20,838 --> 01:59:24,262
- l'm still here.
- Yes, you are, but with dread.

1315
01:59:29,179 --> 01:59:30,942
Give me the order. Come on.

1316
01:59:31,048 --> 01:59:33,778
What is that supposed to do? ls that
supposed to make me not dread you?

1317
01:59:37,054 --> 01:59:39,443
We're in Sicily. lt's opera.

1318
01:59:41,859 --> 01:59:43,258
Okay.

1319
01:59:45,696 --> 01:59:47,755
What do we do now?

1320
01:59:50,568 --> 01:59:52,627
Be reasonable.

1321
01:59:52,736 --> 01:59:54,624
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1322
02:00:02,012 --> 02:00:03,900
l want you to forgive me.

1323
02:00:06,684 --> 02:00:07,742
For what?

1324
02:00:08,852 --> 02:00:10,410
Everything.

1325
02:00:14,692 --> 02:00:16,421
Like God, huh?

1326
02:00:17,661 --> 02:00:20,186
l need something a little closer.

1327
02:00:23,000 --> 02:00:25,855
You couldn't understand
back in those days...

1328
02:00:27,738 --> 02:00:29,660
l loved my father.

1329
02:00:29,773 --> 02:00:32,662
l swore l would never be
a man like him...

1330
02:00:32,776 --> 02:00:35,267
but l loved him,
and he was in danger.

1331
02:00:35,379 --> 02:00:37,267
What could l do?

1332
02:00:37,381 --> 02:00:40,646
And then later
you were in danger.

1333
02:00:40,751 --> 02:00:45,176
Our children were in danger.
What could l do?

1334
02:00:45,289 --> 02:00:48,781
You were all that l... loved...

1335
02:00:48,892 --> 02:00:51,281
valued most in the world.

1336
02:00:52,396 --> 02:00:54,956
And now l'm losing you.
l lost you anyway.

1337
02:00:56,166 --> 02:00:58,054
You're gone...

1338
02:00:59,169 --> 02:01:01,399
and it was all for nothing.

1339
02:01:01,505 --> 02:01:02,904
So--

1340
02:01:06,744 --> 02:01:09,304
You have to understand...

1341
02:01:09,413 --> 02:01:11,904
l had a whole different
destiny planned.

1342
02:01:15,486 --> 02:01:17,681
All right, l'll stop.

1343
02:01:27,898 --> 02:01:31,595
l really don't know what you want
from me, Michael. l really don't know.

1344
02:01:31,702 --> 02:01:36,833
- l mean--
- l'm not the man that you think l am?

1345
02:01:38,375 --> 02:01:42,232
- l don't know.
- l love you, Kay.

1346
02:01:43,447 --> 02:01:46,405
Don't dread me anymore.

1347
02:01:51,355 --> 02:01:53,585
You know...

1348
02:01:53,691 --> 02:01:56,080
every night here in Sicily...

1349
02:01:57,327 --> 02:01:59,022
l dream...

1350
02:02:00,364 --> 02:02:02,753
about my wife
and my children...

1351
02:02:06,003 --> 02:02:08,426
and how l lost them.

1352
02:02:10,107 --> 02:02:13,702
l guess, if it's any consolation...

1353
02:02:13,811 --> 02:02:15,802
l want you to know that...

1354
02:02:19,183 --> 02:02:20,582
that...

1355
02:02:21,852 --> 02:02:24,241
l always loved you, Michael.

1356
02:02:25,589 --> 02:02:28,922
And, you know...

1357
02:02:29,026 --> 02:02:31,415
l always will.

1358
02:03:29,820 --> 02:03:31,549
lt never ends.

1359
02:05:03,847 --> 02:05:05,769
Frederick Keinszig...

1360
02:05:05,883 --> 02:05:08,215
known for a decade as ''God's banker''...

1361
02:05:08,318 --> 02:05:10,240
has been reported missing.

1362
02:05:10,354 --> 02:05:12,242
He was last seen three days ago...

1363
02:05:12,356 --> 02:05:13,755
leaving the Rome offices...

1364
02:05:13,857 --> 02:05:17,623
of a Vatican-owned corporation,
International Immobiliare.

1365
02:05:17,728 --> 02:05:19,753
Also missing was a large sum of money...

1366
02:05:19,863 --> 02:05:21,888
and several documents.

1367
02:05:21,999 --> 02:05:24,388
Come on, Keinszig, you fool.

1368
02:05:28,405 --> 02:05:30,794
Mr. Keinszig's absence casts
further suspicion...

1369
02:05:30,908 --> 02:05:33,331
on the dealings
of the Vatican Bank.

1370
02:05:33,443 --> 02:05:36,276
For several years, the bank
and its subsidiary companies...

1371
02:05:36,380 --> 02:05:40,840
have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.

1372
02:05:43,153 --> 02:05:46,042
Will you please try and understand?

1373
02:05:47,157 --> 02:05:49,079
l have phoned him.

1374
02:05:49,192 --> 02:05:51,581
l have waited here by the phone.

1375
02:05:54,097 --> 02:05:58,830
You would do well to remember,
Mr. Lucchesi...

1376
02:05:58,936 --> 02:06:03,930
that this pope
has very different ideas...

1377
02:06:04,041 --> 02:06:05,997
from the last one.

1378
02:06:27,564 --> 02:06:29,953
Good-bye, my old friend.

1379
02:06:31,668 --> 02:06:34,057
You could've lived
a little longer.

1380
02:06:35,772 --> 02:06:38,661
l could be closer to my dream.

1381
02:06:44,581 --> 02:06:47,141
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1382
02:06:52,155 --> 02:06:56,046
Why was l so feared,
and you were so loved?

1383
02:06:57,160 --> 02:06:59,651
What was it?

1384
02:06:59,730 --> 02:07:01,618
l was no less honorable.

1385
02:07:03,766 --> 02:07:05,654
l wanted to do good.

1386
02:07:09,972 --> 02:07:12,861
What betrayed me?
My mind? My heart?

1387
02:07:15,911 --> 02:07:18,300
Why do l condemn myself so?

1388
02:07:24,820 --> 02:07:29,211
l swear on the lives of my children...

1389
02:07:33,829 --> 02:07:36,718
give me a chance
to redeem myself...

1390
02:07:40,603 --> 02:07:44,494
and l will sin no more.

1391
02:08:07,663 --> 02:08:12,555
You look pale.
Bad news? Tell me right away.

1392
02:08:14,236 --> 02:08:17,763
lt's not just a bad banking deal.

1393
02:08:17,873 --> 02:08:19,761
These guys are butchers.

1394
02:08:21,076 --> 02:08:22,964
What guys?

1395
02:08:23,078 --> 02:08:27,071
Lucchesi--
he controls all of them.

1396
02:08:27,183 --> 02:08:30,072
Altobello, the archbishop...

1397
02:08:31,187 --> 02:08:33,951
other people higher up,
P2, maybe.

1398
02:08:34,056 --> 02:08:37,913
Secret, unknown.
They're running things.

1399
02:08:40,830 --> 02:08:43,719
- l'm in their way.
- Yeah.

1400
02:08:43,833 --> 02:08:46,256
He's hired a professional assassin
to kill you.

1401
02:08:46,368 --> 02:08:47,926
He's Sicilian.

1402
02:08:48,037 --> 02:08:52,428
l don't know his name,
but they say he never fails.

1403
02:08:54,577 --> 02:08:56,465
Then no one is safe.

1404
02:08:59,515 --> 02:09:01,904
Even the new pope
is in danger.

1405
02:09:03,085 --> 02:09:06,976
We still have time.
We can prevent this.

1406
02:09:11,527 --> 02:09:13,415
l tried.

1407
02:09:15,998 --> 02:09:20,890
l tried to keep everything
from coming to this.

1408
02:09:22,071 --> 02:09:27,065
But it's not possible,
not in this world.

1409
02:09:28,177 --> 02:09:30,099
Give me the order.

1410
02:09:33,649 --> 02:09:35,537
You won't be able to go back.

1411
02:09:36,852 --> 02:09:39,980
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1412
02:09:40,089 --> 02:09:43,513
All my life l wanted out.

1413
02:09:43,626 --> 02:09:45,514
l wanted the family out.

1414
02:09:47,363 --> 02:09:49,524
Well, l don't want out.

1415
02:09:49,632 --> 02:09:53,022
l want the power
to preserve the family.

1416
02:09:57,673 --> 02:09:59,561
l'm asking for the order.

1417
02:10:20,629 --> 02:10:22,517
lt's done.

1418
02:10:23,966 --> 02:10:25,888
Because l can't do it anymore.

1419
02:10:30,105 --> 02:10:32,437
Well, it doesn't matter.

1420
02:10:32,541 --> 02:10:35,806
Vincent knows what to do.
Come on outside.

1421
02:10:35,911 --> 02:10:39,335
Take a rest
and don't think about it.

1422
02:10:39,448 --> 02:10:42,337
- All l do is think about it.
- l'm your son.

1423
02:10:43,619 --> 02:10:45,507
Command me in all things.

1424
02:10:48,123 --> 02:10:50,011
Give up my daughter.

1425
02:10:53,095 --> 02:10:54,983
That's the price you pay...

1426
02:10:56,265 --> 02:10:58,995
for the life you choose.

1427
02:11:24,727 --> 02:11:26,615
Nephew...

1428
02:11:28,597 --> 02:11:30,485
from this moment on...

1429
02:11:32,434 --> 02:11:34,322
call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1430
02:11:39,441 --> 02:11:40,840
Sit.

1431
02:13:46,935 --> 02:13:50,063
l know how you feel about Michael...

1432
02:13:50,172 --> 02:13:52,003
but you can't save him.

1433
02:13:52,107 --> 02:13:53,995
He's lost.

1434
02:13:55,711 --> 02:13:57,201
Think of yourself.

1435
02:13:58,514 --> 02:14:00,903
What's your answer?

1436
02:14:03,118 --> 02:14:05,006
Enjoy the opera.

1437
02:14:07,055 --> 02:14:08,943
lt's all taken care of.

1438
02:14:13,795 --> 02:14:16,184
Check the bar.
l'll check the top floor.

1439
02:14:20,502 --> 02:14:23,391
''Here's hoping Tony sings better
at the Theatro Massimo...

1440
02:14:23,505 --> 02:14:25,894
than he does in the shower--
Love, Douglas.''

1441
02:14:27,676 --> 02:14:29,564
My darling, Costanza.

1442
02:14:32,314 --> 02:14:34,703
- This is a great occasion.
- Come, sit down.

1443
02:14:39,821 --> 02:14:41,709
Happy birthday.

1444
02:14:41,823 --> 02:14:44,348
You're 80 years old,
you don't look more than 60.

1445
02:14:44,459 --> 02:14:46,086
You're the only one
who remembered.

1446
02:14:46,195 --> 02:14:48,561
Michael, we just got the word.

1447
02:14:48,664 --> 02:14:51,861
The pope's ratifying
the lmmobiliare deal. We've won.

1448
02:14:51,967 --> 02:14:53,855
Congratulations.

1449
02:14:56,638 --> 02:14:59,027
How strange, the way things work.

1450
02:14:59,141 --> 02:15:02,531
The pope's doing exactly what you said
he'd do. He's cleaning house.

1451
02:15:04,046 --> 02:15:08,608
He should be careful.
lt's dangerous to be an honest man.

1452
02:15:14,089 --> 02:15:16,478
l wanna put more muscle backstage
with Tony.

1453
02:15:29,204 --> 02:15:32,594
On your birthday,
you used to shower me with treats.

1454
02:15:32,708 --> 02:15:34,596
Tootsie Rolls.

1455
02:15:35,711 --> 02:15:38,669
The nuns who made these cannolis
took a vow of silence.

1456
02:15:38,780 --> 02:15:41,340
They're the very finest.

1457
02:15:46,755 --> 02:15:48,154
Hey, cous.

1458
02:15:51,159 --> 02:15:52,592
Where's your leather?

1459
02:15:56,331 --> 02:15:57,764
Stop it.

1460
02:16:03,939 --> 02:16:06,828
You're so thin.
You eat it.

1461
02:16:30,732 --> 02:16:35,123
lt's over. There are things l have to do
that you can't be a part of.

1462
02:16:35,237 --> 02:16:38,331
Don't look at your father. lt's not
your father's decision. lt's mine.

1463
02:16:40,075 --> 02:16:42,464
Don't hate your father.

1464
02:16:44,246 --> 02:16:48,068
There are things l wanna be a part of,
you can't be around.

1465
02:16:50,118 --> 02:16:52,507
After tonight,
you won't see me anymore.

1466
02:16:57,326 --> 02:17:00,022
You gotta understand.
You gotta understand.

1467
02:17:01,897 --> 02:17:03,785
l'll always love you.

1468
02:17:16,712 --> 02:17:18,202
Love somebody else.

1469
02:17:40,969 --> 02:17:42,857
- To Tony.
- To Tony.

1470
02:20:59,701 --> 02:21:03,762
- They won't try.anything.
- Yeah, everything is fine. lt's clear.

1471
02:21:03,872 --> 02:21:06,932
l've already sent Al Neri
to the Vatican.

1472
02:23:56,344 --> 02:23:58,574
Check out the side.

1473
02:26:22,123 --> 02:26:25,012
Good. You got him.

1474
02:27:16,878 --> 02:27:19,267
Tonight the Corleone family
settles its accounts.

1475
02:27:20,381 --> 02:27:22,303
Keinszig...

1476
02:27:22,417 --> 02:27:25,875
that little Swiss banker fuck.

1477
02:27:25,987 --> 02:27:30,651
He's been swindling everyone
from the beginning. Fuck him.

1478
02:27:31,592 --> 02:27:33,480
Don Lucchesi, my friend...

1479
02:27:34,429 --> 02:27:37,353
Calo will pay him a visit
at his home.

1480
02:27:39,634 --> 02:27:42,523
Neri, take a train to Rome.

1481
02:27:44,605 --> 02:27:46,493
Light a candle
for the archbishop.

1482
02:29:49,897 --> 02:29:53,355
Michael, it's serious.
Our man inside the Vatican says...

1483
02:29:53,468 --> 02:29:54,867
there's a plot
against the pope.

1484
02:29:54,969 --> 02:29:57,130
You mean, he's gonna have
a heart attack?

1485
02:30:04,412 --> 02:30:09,304
This pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1486
02:30:12,553 --> 02:30:13,952
Let's go back to the opera.

1487
02:32:38,866 --> 02:32:39,924
Sleep.

1488
02:32:41,135 --> 02:32:43,023
Sleep, Godfather.

1489
02:36:32,366 --> 02:36:34,561
- l like this outfit.
- Yeah, l figured you would.

1490
02:36:34,668 --> 02:36:37,159
- Bravo. Say hello.
- Thank you.

1491
02:36:43,344 --> 02:36:45,574
- Did you like it?
- Great.

1492
02:36:47,414 --> 02:36:49,746
Let's get out of here.

1493
02:36:59,326 --> 02:37:03,092
- Can l please talk to you now?
- Not now, it's not a good time.

1494
02:37:03,197 --> 02:37:07,088
- You're just like my father.
- Come on, stay with the family. Go on.

1495
02:37:08,636 --> 02:37:10,399
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1496
02:37:10,504 --> 02:37:14,395
ln about one minute, there's gonna be
carabinieri crawling all over the place.

1497
02:37:15,709 --> 02:37:18,269
Okay. Let's get everybody
to the cars, nice and quiet.

1498
02:37:18,379 --> 02:37:20,267
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1499
02:37:34,895 --> 02:37:37,989
When they hear the name Corleone,
they're gonna think of a voice.

1500
02:37:47,942 --> 02:37:49,637
Dad.

1501
02:37:57,618 --> 02:37:59,108
This is my mom.

1502
02:38:08,462 --> 02:38:12,489
Dad, why are you doing this to me?

1503
02:38:21,542 --> 02:38:24,966
- Go on, move back. Go on, move back.
- Hey, move!

1504
02:38:25,079 --> 02:38:28,276
- You don't have to do this to me.
- Doing what?

1505
02:38:28,382 --> 02:38:30,976
What do you mean?

